This paper deals with the issue of ad-blocking and anti-adblocking mechanisms, which is primarily related to computer security (cs.CR) and web technologies (cs.WEB). The authors also use network analysis techniques to identify third-party services shared across multiple websites, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves data analysis and processing, which can be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the authors analyze the impact of anti-adblocking on multimedia content, which can be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
